.TH "of_clk_set_defaults" 9 "of_clk_set_defaults" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_clk_set_defaults \- parse and set assigned clocks configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_clk_set_defaults
.BI "(struct device_node *node "  ","
.BI "bool clk_supplier "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "node" 12
device node to apply clock settings for
.IP "clk_supplier" 12
true if clocks supplied by \fInode\fP should also be considered
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function parses 'assigned-{clocks/clock-parents/clock-rates}' properties
and sets any specified clock parents and rates. The \fIclk_supplier\fP argument
should be set to true if \fInode\fP may be also a clock supplier of any clock
listed in its 'assigned-clocks' or 'assigned-clock-parents' properties.
If \fIclk_supplier\fP is false the function exits returning 0 as soon as it
determines the \fInode\fP is also a supplier of any of the clocks.
